edu.stanford.folding.msmexplorer.io
Class NewlineDelimitedReader

java.lang.Object
  edu.stanford.folding.msmexplorer.io.NewlineDelimitedReader

public class NewlineDelimitedReader
extends java.lang.Object

A class to read generic newline delimited files. Should be useful for reading in axes labels, mapping files, other simple one-to-one data files.

Method Detail

read

public static java.lang.Object[] read(java.lang.String filePath)
Read the newline delimited file at location filePath. Returns the file contents in an object array. Determines what kind of data is in the file (currently supports ints, floats/doubles, and Strings (i.e. other)) by looking at the first token in the file and assuming the entire file is composed of tokens of that type. Failures generate dialog warnings that (sort of) attempt to explain the failure.

Parameters:
filePath - string location of where to find file to open
Returns:
the contents in the file as a file array
